- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the information content of a binary vector passed through a noisy channel.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper discusses Boolean functions and their properties.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of computing the most informative Boolean function.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper discusses the effect of a noisy channel on a binary vector, which is relevant to cryptography and security.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial objects such as binary vectors and Boolean functions.
